President Donald Trump had a friendly conversation with President Rodrigo Duterte of the Philippines, during which they discussed the concerns of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) regarding regional security, particularly the threat posed by North Korea. They also talked about the Philippine government's efforts to combat drug-related issues. President Trump expressed his enjoyment of the conversation and expressed his intention to visit the Philippines in November for the East Asia Summit and the U.S.-ASEAN Summit. Additionally, President Trump invited President Duterte to the White House to discuss the positive direction of the United States-Philippines alliance.